label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 175: Figure de sistemi del mondo d'Aristotile, Copernico, e Ticone
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Diagrams representing the Ptolemaic (referred to as Aristotelian in the title) and Copernican theories of the universe, with a final diagram representing the theory of Tycho Brahe.
        Language: Italian, with Latin for some figure numbers
        Support: paper
        Extent: 
        Collation: Paper, 22; 1⁴(-1 for pastedown) 2¹⁰ 3¹⁰(-1 for pastedown).
        Layout: 
        Script: Title and figure numbers written in humanistic script; text in one figure written in cursive script (f. 7v).
        Decoration: 46 diagrams in ink or pen and wash; in diagrams including the sun, the sun is drawn more elaborately, with a face; title written in gold, surrounded by a cartouche in pen and wash (f. 3r). The diagrams are numbered, restarting at the beginning of the Copernican section (f. 14r), but the Copernican diagrams are not all in numerical order.
        Binding: Limp parchment.
        Origin: Written in Italy, ca. 1680.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 175
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5848812 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5848812
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs175.html
